<main>
    <div class="home-title">
        <h1>Secure Oil Price API Demo</h1>
    </div>
    <section class="hero">
        <p>
            This INF 653 project demonstrates a practical, secure API built with Node.js and Express.
            The goal is to show how layered middleware enforces security checks before any oil-price data is returned.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section class="about-container">
        <h2>Overview</h2>
        <p>
            This app exposes an oil-price data endpoint and protects it with middleware that validates requests.
            Only requests that meet multiple security conditions are allowed to receive data.
        </p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Authentication:</strong> Bearer token verification to ensure callers are authorized.</li>
            <li><strong>IP Filtering:</strong> Requests must originate from configured, allowed IP addresses.</li>
            <li><strong>CORS Control:</strong> Only permitted origins may access the API from browsers.</li>
            <li><strong>Request Validation:</strong> Input checks and error responses for malformed or unauthorized calls.</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="how-to-container">
        <h2>Design & Architecture</h2>
        <p>
            This app uses an Express middleware chain so each concern (auth, IP, CORS, logging) is isolated and testable.
            Data returned by the API is intentionally minimal and can be swapped for live sources in future work.
        </p>
        <h2>How to use basic auth</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>Navigate to the Dashboard page.</li>
            <li>Enter your username and password.</li>
            <li>View the oil price data in the page.</li>
        </ol>
        <h2>How to get Bearer token</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>Navigate to the Login page.</li>
            <li>Follow the instructions there.</li>
            <li>Get the oil prices data using the token and the api/oil-prices endpoint.</li>
        </ol>
    </section>
</main>